Cape Town's iconic Table Mountain has made it into the finals of the World Travel Awards. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Cape Town's iconic Table Mountain has made it into the finals of the World Travel Awards. The landmark has numerous awards already under its belt including winning the African leg of the competition. READ: City to tackle Table Mountain attacks However, it faces stiff competition from India's Taj Mahal, The Great Wall of China and Machu Picchu in Peru. It has previously been voted as one of the world’s Seven Wonders of Nature. Voting for the awards closes at the end of October and the winner will be announced in Oman in November.